nt color=#FF0000>(8/8/01 10:21:02 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouselaboratory.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2005.topic>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://communities.msn.com/_Secure/0MgAAABIRF7ddMGbLmK6nXDlaCTN5Byei0osLS85Q8l!O0SN3*berQl1ZGEhJaytdp7Wd!OoQjIOmRaXFEJ1dYg/sig.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Poison duration on npc's</span><hr size=1> I've been doing a lot of testing with a few different poisons on many high level npc's.  Results aren't good.  I have 250 make and 200 apply poison.  Every time I get a poison to land on them it only lasts for a few seconds before wearing off, even if it has a 3 min duration.  Tests were with paralyze 3 and dizzy 4 on sontalak, yelinak, aaryonar, derekor the vindicator, statue of rallos zek and cazic thule.  Cazic resists everything I throw at him so that's pretty straight forward, sucks.  Even though I've been told CT can be slowed by us he's resisted all of about 20 paralyze 3's, all after malo.  On the rest of the mobs I listed, poison sticks though.  I've personally slowed them all and even though it's supposed to last 102 seconds it only lasts for about 3-5 seconds, no dispells or other debuffs cast that would cancel it.  I've used dizzy 4 on sontalak and yelinak.  Funny thing happened on sont, it said my spell didn't take hold.  No other debuffs cast on him that would block it.  It took hold on yelinak but again lasted only 3 seconds.  Testing on pc's, I used paralyze 1 on a 60 pally in guild and supposed to last 42 seconds, lasted 3 seconds.  Used paralyze 3 on a 60 war in guild and it lasted around the full 102 seconds, didnt' track time on that one but lasted a while.  Used dizzy 4 on a 60 ranger in guild and it lasted the full 3 min duration exactly.  The ranger lowered his pr really low for the test, the others were at normal pr levels.  I've been speculating that they made rogue poisons get checked for resist every few seconds and not just the initial proc.  This really blows for us and I think we should speak up about this and find out what is really going on. <p>Crillan Kidneypoker<BR>60 Human Rogue of Valon<BR>Terris Thule</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/umorchaint.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Morchaint</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(8/9/01 9:49:37 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouselaboratory.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2005.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Poison duration on npc's</span><hr size=1> I have a feeling that our poisons check for resists every 'tick'. I've used snare poisons on glimmer drakes in ToV and while the poison will land, it never lasts anywhere near the full duration, so it's not a reliable snare in the least. (Usually it just delays the mob a bit so it can't run *quite* as far). Is it possible that we have the durations wrong? Either that or big mobs all carry cure poison potions on them. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br>If a resistance check MUST be made for 'balance' reasons, the mob should have a severe penalty once the poison has taken hold and higher level poisons should be harder to resist. This would give some kind of incentive to work up past a skill of 30. After all, a harder to make poison should be more toxic.<br><br>Morchaint Poisonblade<br>&lt;Looking Glass&gt;<br>Ayonae Ro <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ucrillan.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Crillan</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(8/13/01 5:05:03 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouselaboratory.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2005.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://communities.msn.com/_Secure/0MgAAABIRF7ddMGbLmK6nXDlaCTN5Byei0osLS85Q8l!O0SN3*berQl1ZGEhJaytdp7Wd!OoQjIOmRaXFEJ1dYg/sig.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Poison duration on npc's</span><hr size=1> The effects and durations are taken straight from the spdat file so they are correct. <p>Crillan Kidneypoker<BR>60 Human Rogue of Valon<BR>Terris Thule</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uorthaanc.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Orthaanc</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(8/14/01 6:47:09 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouselaboratory.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2005.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Poison duration on npc's</span><hr size=1> Haven't multiple Verant employees commented on how the spdat file may not be completely correct?<br><br>just wondering<br>Orthaanc<br>lvl38 Wood Elf Rogue Rodcet Nife <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ucrillan.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Crillan</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(8/14/01 11:27:28 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouselaboratory.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2005.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://communities.msn.com/_Secure/0MgAAABIRF7ddMGbLmK6nXDlaCTN5Byei0osLS85Q8l!O0SN3*berQl1ZGEhJaytdp7Wd!OoQjIOmRaXFEJ1dYg/sig.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Poison duration on npc's</span><hr siz