#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/usaejorn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Saejorn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(7/27/02 6:06:21 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouselaboratory.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2005.topic&index=9>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://ross.finch.st/signatures/eq/saejorn_dirks.jpeg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Poison duration on npc's</span><hr size=1> btw, on the sk board, we noticed our tap stat stealing spells are also wearing off almost immediately (like *now* to a tick later). <p><center><table cellpadding="3" border="0" cellspacing="0" width="450"><tr>  <td colspan="3">    <hr>  </td></tr><tr>  <td align="center" valign="center" width="150">    <a href="http://www.eq-mk.com" target="new"><img src="http://ross.finch.st/signatures/eq/mkmlogo2.jpeg" border="0"></a><br>    Mystic Knights<br>    <i>The little guild that could.</i>  </td>  <td align="center" valign="center">    <b>Saejorn T'Kaarn</b><br>    54 Rogue    <p>    <b>Xulan Du'Traix</b><br>    55 SK  </td>  <td align="center" valign="center" width="150">    <a href="http://leagueofguilds.ohgo.com" target="new"><img src="http://ross.finch.st/signatures/eq/sword5.jpeg" border="0"></a><br>    Tarew Marr<br>    League of Guilds  </td></tr></table></center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uuroninsertpunhere.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Uron    insert pun here</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(8/15/02 1:38:20 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouselaboratory.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2005.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Poison duration on npc's</span><hr size=1> Whether the spelldat files are correct on duration or not is irrelevant really.. if the poison lands it should either last the full duration, (whatever it may be, but I can't believe 3 sec duration is tagged as max), or have a <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> chance</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> to wear off at half duration at the earliest, certainly not wear off in one tick.<br><br>Poisonmaking and the use of poison on a semi regular basis is already such a pain, and then when you go through all that and actually get one to land, the effect checks to see if it breaks <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> every</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> tick?  That seems pretty ridiculous to me, and unacceptable.  Think of it from a RL perspective:  if someone poisons me with arsenic and it's a significant enough dose to affect me, I'm not suddenly going to 'get better' 6 seconds later for no apparent reason.  It would be a little more understandable that a huge mystical creature like a dragon could purge its system of the poison, but this happens with every mob.  Don't tell me some retarded werewolf on steroids guarding ol VS should be able to purge its system of dire poisons on command.. that is ridiculous.<br><br>Also, AA skill poison mastery should, imo, make poisons that the player with this skill makes either last 150% as long, or be 150% more effective while they do last.  (decision as to which one needs to be made, not either effect randomly) This would make this skill much more desirable and be more in line with having to spend that many AA pts to get.  Right now it's a joke imo.<br><br>I really like the clues that I've seen that poison might be made into a 'proc-buff'.  Then it would be worth using.  In the one-shot-wear-off-randomly form it's in now, I don't even bother using it, I have better uses for my inventory space than this poor joke of a poison system, thanks.<br><br> - Branagh Blackthorn -<br> <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :evil --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/devil.gif ALT=":evil"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  the black thorn on the White Rose <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :evil --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/devil.gif ALT=":evil"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uishkurleroux.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ishkur Leroux</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(8/15/02 1:48:00 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouselaboratory.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2005.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Poison duration on npc's</span><hr size=1> I have to agree with you on this, although the chances of me ceasin' to use poisons are goin' to be slim to none.<br><br>Granted, poisonin' does have its uses in the game.  Hell, I believe since Rogues are not exactly meant to fight a mob head-on, the intentions for poisons are either to escape alive or to catch a mob off guard with it so that its death is possible.<br><br>However, the problems that I've seen with poisons have been either duration, resists, and/or the application factor.  There are NO SET FACTORS that determine what will insure full duration of the poison.  I've heard that the Apply Poison skill is supposed to be the determinin' factor in whether a poison lands at full duration or not.  Verant nor anyone else in the EQ staff has determined this to be true, so we can only assume that it's merely for the success/failure of the poison coatin' the weapon.<br><br>This makes the world of poisonin' unreliable and very sporadic, causin' many Rogues to rely solely on damage distribution.  If the tick check continues, there's no way to determine how long the poison duration is supposed to be with certain mobs.  Why bother usin' them if a poison like Lethargic Bliss (Snare for 5secs a tick with each tick per level you are) when it isn't gonna last?  Same for any DoT.  The only &quot;fullproof&quot; poison seems to be the DD ones and there's a 50/50 chance for that.  You either hit or don't, haven't seen any partial damage for that.<br><br>If that isn't worse, there's the Apply Poison factor.  It's a joke to work.  I've been fail free since 80 and apparently you can apply poison with a skill of 80 for a poison that's gonna take 200+ to make.  I'm not a genius or anythin' but wouldn't it be harder to poison a weapon with a poison that's very hard and thus very toxic?  Plus, Poison Mastery is goin' to serious waste.  See, it takes you a lot of points to get to Poison Mastery 3, the epitome of poison application with applies takin' 2.5-3 seconds, and yet, you have to SIT?  I don't think it takes sittin' to apply, whatever.  But I firmly believe that at Poison Mastery 3 you should be able to apply by just standin'.  That would make it SOMEWHAT worthwhile at this current state.<br><br>Thin's they can do to make poisonin' better?  Well the first is removin' the tick situation.  What they should do is perform one check that will take place durin' half the poison's duration or somethin'.  And they should make the resist take place with REALLY high poisonin'.  I think it's rather messed up that someone with 50 resist and is a few levels lower than me can resist my poison and hit me full flush with a spell e'en though I have 100+ MR.<br><br>Another thin', make Apply Poison a factor.  Sometimes I think the resists and the short durations stem from the fact that I haven't coated it enough.  Might start applyin' 2 doses of the same poison just to be certain.  There was a game that determined whether poisons would hit or not based on the application skill.  The equation was poisoned food or drinks were equal to the percent of the skill.  Like if my poisonin' was at 70, then I had a 70% chance of success.  Poisoned weapons had a 1/4 chance of that percentage.  So if I was a 100% poisoner, my weapon had 25% chance of landin'.  Now that would be a bit ridiculous with the poison-buff thin's goin' on, but sometihin' similar that would increase it to a 5% chance when maxed out and a 10% chance per hit with Poison Mastery, it would be lovely.<br><br>And one more thin', poison is supposed to be subtle and a gradual decrease in the person's life.  It disturbs me when I see a poisoned mob jump at me the moment I poison it when it's my first touch.<br><br>Ishkur Leroux<br>&quot;The True Meanin' of Poisonin' is still missin'.&quot; <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouselaboratory.showPrevMessage?topicID=2005.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouselaboratory.showNextMessage?topicID=2005.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouselaboratory.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2005.topic&index=11><img src=http://216.40.211.42/images/reply.jpg border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouselaboratory.emailToFriend?topicID=2005.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouselaboratory.threadControl?topicID=2005.topic><img src=http://216.40.211.42/images/dagger.jpg border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/f